              MIME 561 Advanced Materials Design (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-30436" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mining &amp; Materials Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mining &amp; Materials Engineering              : Advanced topics in materials design problems. Discussion and laboratory work, supplemented by detailed technical reports. Special attention is given to selection, design and failure problems in various materials systems.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
